# Aegis AI – Local LLM Assistant Platform

## Overview

Aegis AI is a self-hosted Large Language Model platform designed to provide private AI conversations, memory management, document retrieval, agent workflows, and local model inference without depending on external AI APIs.

The platform combines a modern web interface, FastAPI backend, local Transformer-based LLM execution, vector memory storage, Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), and agent-based orchestration into a single architecture.

The primary objective of the project is to create a secure and extensible AI ecosystem where users can run open-source models such as Mistral 7B locally while maintaining full ownership of data and conversations.

---

# Project Objectives

* Run open-source LLMs locally
* Eliminate dependency on cloud AI providers
* Support conversational memory
* Enable Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)
* Provide document-based knowledge retrieval
* Create an extensible AI agent architecture
* Support future tool integrations
* Maintain user privacy through local execution

